{
  "info": {
    "name": "EduSpace Edge API",
    "description": "Two request groups:\n\n1. **Device -> Edge API** — what an ESP32 device sends to the edge (`X-API-Key` auth). Start the edge in development mode (`$env:EDUSPACE_ENV=\"development\"; flask --app src.app run`) so the test device is seeded on the first request. Test device: device_id `esp32-aula-101`, X-API-Key `test-api-key-edu`.\n\n2. **Edge -> Backend forward (simulated)** — reproduces the call the edge makes to the cloud backend (eduspace-platform). Use it to test the backend receiver, including the `X-Edge-Key` shared-secret header the edge sends when `EDUSPACE_FORWARD_AUTH` is set. See docs/backend-integration-guide.md.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "baseUrl",
      "value": "http://localhost:5000",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "apiKey",
      "value": "test-api-key-edu",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "backendUrl",
      "value": "http://localhost:5283/api/v1/iot-monitoring/sensor-readings",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "edgeKey",
      "value": "edge-secret",
      "type": "string"
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Device -> Edge API",
      "description": "Requests a classroom device sends to the edge service. Auth: X-API-Key.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Submit reading (201 Created)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "X-API-Key", "value": "{{apiKey}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"device_id\": \"esp32-aula-101\",\n  \"temperature\": 31.5,\n  \"humidity\": 70.0,\n  \"occupancy\": true\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/iot-monitoring/sensor-readings",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "iot-monitoring", "sensor-readings"]
            },
            "description": "Happy path. Returns 201 with {reading_id, alert_led_state, recorded_at}. `recorded_at` is optional; omit it to let the server timestamp the reading."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status is 201', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
                  "const b = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('has reading_id', () => pm.expect(b).to.have.property('reading_id'));",
                  "pm.test('has alert_led_state', () => pm.expect(b).to.have.property('alert_led_state'));",
                  "pm.test('has recorded_at', () => pm.expect(b).to.have.property('recorded_at'));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Submit reading with explicit recorded_at (201)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "X-API-Key", "value": "{{apiKey}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"device_id\": \"esp32-aula-101\",\n  \"temperature\": 22.0,\n  \"humidity\": 45.0,\n  \"occupancy\": false,\n  \"recorded_at\": \"2026-06-06T14:30:00Z\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/iot-monitoring/sensor-readings",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "iot-monitoring", "sensor-readings"]
            },
            "description": "Client-supplied ISO 8601 timestamp. The server normalizes it to UTC and echoes it back in recorded_at."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status is 201', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Validation error (400) - temperature out of range",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "X-API-Key", "value": "{{apiKey}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"device_id\": \"esp32-aula-101\",\n  \"temperature\": 999,\n  \"humidity\": 70.0,\n  \"occupancy\": true\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/iot-monitoring/sensor-readings",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "iot-monitoring", "sensor-readings"]
            },
            "description": "temperature must be between -40 and 85; humidity between 0 and 100; occupancy must be a boolean. This sends temperature=999 and expects 400."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status is 400', () => pm.response.to.have.status(400));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Validation error (400) - missing field",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "X-API-Key", "value": "{{apiKey}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"device_id\": \"esp32-aula-101\",\n  \"temperature\": 25.0\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/iot-monitoring/sensor-readings",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "iot-monitoring", "sensor-readings"]
            },
            "description": "Missing required humidity and occupancy fields. Expects 400."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status is 400', () => pm.response.to.have.status(400));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Auth failure (401) - wrong API key",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "X-API-Key", "value": "wrong-key" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"device_id\": \"esp32-aula-101\",\n  \"temperature\": 25.0,\n  \"humidity\": 50.0,\n  \"occupancy\": true\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/iot-monitoring/sensor-readings",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "iot-monitoring", "sensor-readings"]
            },
            "description": "Invalid X-API-Key. Returns a generic 401 (no detail leaked)."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status is 401', () => pm.response.to.have.status(401));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Auth failure (401) - missing API key",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"device_id\": \"esp32-aula-101\",\n  \"temperature\": 25.0,\n  \"humidity\": 50.0,\n  \"occupancy\": true\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/iot-monitoring/sensor-readings",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "iot-monitoring", "sensor-readings"]
            },
            "description": "No X-API-Key header at all. Returns 401."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status is 401', () => pm.response.to.have.status(401));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Edge -> Backend forward (simulated)",
      "description": "Reproduces the POST the edge sends to the cloud backend (eduspace-platform). The body is the edge's forwarded payload (note: snake_case keys, and `reading_id` is the edge-local id). Auth is the `X-Edge-Key` shared secret the edge sends when `EDUSPACE_FORWARD_AUTH` is set; it must match the backend's `Edge:ApiKey`. Point {{backendUrl}} at your backend endpoint.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Forward reading to backend (2xx)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "X-Edge-Key", "value": "{{edgeKey}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"reading_id\": 42,\n  \"device_id\": \"esp32-aula-101\",\n  \"temperature\": 31.5,\n  \"humidity\": 70.0,\n  \"occupancy\": true,\n  \"alert_led_state\": 1,\n  \"recorded_at\": \"2026-06-06T14:30:00+00:00\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{backendUrl}}",
              "host": ["{{backendUrl}}"]
            },
            "description": "The exact payload shape the edge forwards. Backend should persist it and return 2xx (200 or 201). The edge treats ONLY 2xx as success."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status is 2xx', () => pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.within(200, 299));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Duplicate forward is idempotent (2xx)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "X-Edge-Key", "value": "{{edgeKey}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"reading_id\": 42,\n  \"device_id\": \"esp32-aula-101\",\n  \"temperature\": 31.5,\n  \"humidity\": 70.0,\n  \"occupancy\": true,\n  \"alert_led_state\": 1,\n  \"recorded_at\": \"2026-06-06T14:30:00+00:00\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{backendUrl}}",
              "host": ["{{backendUrl}}"]
            },
            "description": "Send the SAME (device_id, reading_id) again — simulates a retry after a lost 2xx. Backend must NOT create a second row and must still return 2xx, otherwise the edge would retry forever."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status is 2xx (duplicate accepted)', () => pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.within(200, 299));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Missing X-Edge-Key (401)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"reading_id\": 99,\n  \"device_id\": \"esp32-aula-101\",\n  \"temperature\": 25.0,\n  \"humidity\": 50.0,\n  \"occupancy\": true,\n  \"alert_led_state\": 0,\n  \"recorded_at\": \"2026-06-06T15:00:00+00:00\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{backendUrl}}",
              "host": ["{{backendUrl}}"]
            },
            "description": "No X-Edge-Key header. Expects 401 once the backend's EdgeApiKeyFilter is enabled. (If the filter is not yet implemented, this returns 2xx — that's expected until you add it.)"
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status is 401 (filter enabled)', () => pm.response.to.have.status(401));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Wrong X-Edge-Key (401)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "X-Edge-Key", "value": "not-the-secret" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"reading_id\": 100,\n  \"device_id\": \"esp32-aula-101\",\n  \"temperature\": 25.0,\n  \"humidity\": 50.0,\n  \"occupancy\": true,\n  \"alert_led_state\": 0,\n  \"recorded_at\": \"2026-06-06T15:05:00+00:00\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{backendUrl}}",
              "host": ["{{backendUrl}}"]
            },
            "description": "Wrong shared secret. Expects 401 once the backend's EdgeApiKeyFilter is enabled."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status is 401 (filter enabled)', () => pm.response.to.have.status(401));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
